text: Alina Goreac (born September 28, 1952) is a retired Romanian artistic gymnast who represented Romania at the 1972 Olympic Games.Sports Reference Alina Goreac During her career she medaled on all four events (floor, balance beam, vault and uneven bars) at European championshipsGymn Forum 1973 European Artistic Gymnastics Championships Women’s Events FinalsGymn Forum 1975 European Artistic Gymnastics Championships Women’s Events Finals and was the 1977 University Games all around and uneven bars champion.Gymn Forum Alina Goreac Since 1981 she has been a gymnastics coach. ==References== ==External links== *List of competitive results Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:People from Lugoj Category:Romanian female artistic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1972 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Romania Category:Romanian gymnastics coaches Category:Universiade medalists in gymnastics Category:Universiade gold medalists for Romania Category:Medalists at the 1977 Summer Universiade
